The paper deals with software development effort estimation, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed model is a hybrid intelligent model that combines a neural network model with a fuzzy model, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The model is designed to improve the accuracy of software cost estimation, which is a common problem in software engineering, and the use of machine learning techniques such as neural networks and fuzzy logic is a common approach to solving this problem (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of handling uncertain and imprecise inputs, which is a common issue in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed model is evaluated using published project and industrial data, which involves system-level analysis and evaluation (cs.SY).
